article.headline: James Madison 63, N.C.-Wilmington 54
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Denzel Bowles scored 21 points and grabbed 11 rebounds to lead James Madison to a 63-54 victory over North Carolina-Wilmington on Saturday night. Bowles finished 10 for 13 from the floor (76.9 percent) en route to his ninth double-double of the year. The Dukes (15-3, 5-1 Colonial Athletic Association) led 25-21 at halftime despite shooting 10 for 32 from the floor (31.3 percent), including 2 for 13 from 3-point range (15.4 percent). James Madison stretched its lead to 63-49 -- the largest of the contest -- with 2:21 left to play as the Dukes remained undefeated at home this season (9-0). Devon Moore scored 14 points and Julius Wells added 12 for the Dukes, who have won nine straight games. Humpty Hitchens added a career-high nine assists for James Madison. Chad Tomko had 17 points and Keith Rendleman added 13 for the Seahawks (9-8, 3-3).
